### Base URL Configuration
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@contentType = application/json

### Variables for testing
@userId = 1
@userEmail = test@example.com
@userPassword = password123456

### CREATE USER
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "{{userEmail}}",
  "password": "{{userPassword}}",
  "roleId": "USER"
}

### 2. CREATE ADMIN USER
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Admin User",
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "admin123456",
  "roleId": "ADMIN"
}

### 4. GET ALL USERS
GET {{baseUrl}}/users


### 9. GET USERS BY ROLE - USER
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/role/USER

### 10. GET USERS BY ROLE - ADMIN
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/role/ADMIN

### 12. GET SINGLE USER BY ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}

### 14. UPDATE USER
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

